title: Top netters in Philta tilt at V’Verde
text:
by Kristel Satumbaga
October 5, 2015 Top Filipino netters go up against their foreign counterparts starting today when the main draw of the Philippine Sports Commission (PSC)-Philta Men’s International Futures fires off at the Valle Verde Country Club shell court in Pasig City.
Jeson Patrombon banners the small field after automatically getting a main draw slot with his No. 1204 International Tennis Federation (ITF) singles rankings.
Joining him were wildcard entries Patrick John Tierro, Kyle Dandan, Johnny Arcilla and Francis Casey Alcantara, who all didn’t have ITF men’s rankings.
Tierro and Arcilla were veteran Davis Cuppers, Dandan was a former age-grouper and Alcantara is an Australian Open junior doubles champion in 2009.
Meanwhile, qualifying to the main draw were Fil-Spaniard Diego Dalisay, who survived Shu Saito of Japan, 4-6, 6-1, 6-4, and Elbert Anasta, a 6-0, 6-3 winner over Indonesia’s Ming Tham.
